U.K. Helicopter maker &lt;Westland Plc> willreduce the 6,000 workforce of its helicopter division by arounda third over the next few weeks, a company spokesman said.    He said the decision was in part the result of a 400 mlnstg government order for military helicopters announcedearlier.    The spokesman said the order had reduced the number ofredundancies necessary but was not large enough to avoid joblosses. The total group workforce is 11,000. The company wasrescued last year by a consortium of United Technologies Corp's&lt;UTX.N> Sikorsky unit and Fiat SpA &lt;FIAT.MI>. Reuter&#3;